<p>&nbsp;</p><p>Welcome to Cooking Soc!</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>We're Katie and Rosie and we will be running the society this year!</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>This year, we are running sessions once a month and on a pay-as-you-go basis so that there's no massive commitments (we know you're all busy!)</p><p>All the while, the Cooking Soc page serves as our community page: we'll post session events, and you guys can post recipes, ideas, pictures of delicious food or whatever else you fancy contributing!</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>Some ideas we have for sessions:&nbsp;</p><ul><li>Microwave cakes/Study snacks&nbsp;</li><li>Pizza!</li><li>Salad competition (salad is a loose term in our household - it can literally be anything)</li><li>Ready Steady Cook (you all bring ingredients and Rosie and Katie battle to make the best meal Butler has ever seen)&nbsp;</li><li>Rice dishes (we provide the rice, you guys make it more exciting)&nbsp;</li><li>Pasta dishes</li><li>Soup competition&nbsp;</li><li>Food festival (selling food to raise money for Grace House)</li><li>Indian/Cooking soc night</li><li>Tapas night</li><li>And we would also like to hold some socials! (Christmas dinner, bar crawls etc.)&nbsp;</li></ul><p>For some sessions we may ask you to bring a couple of pounds, and for others we may ask you to bring your own ingredients, but most importantly we AREN'T asking for membership costs *despite what it says above* so there's no commitment!&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>If you have any questions or contributions feel free to email either of us at: <a href="mailto:k.r.greig@durham.ac.uk">k.r.greig@durham.ac.uk</a>&nbsp;or <a href="mailto:r.l.e.keates@dur.ac.uk">r.l.e.keates@dur.ac.uk</a>&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>See you in October!!</p>